<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a179193-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s3211"><num value="3211">§ 3211.</num><heading> Relationship to other authority</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to limit or affect any authority of the Secretary or the Commission under any other provision of law.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a179194-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/617/tIII/s311">Pub. L. 95–617, title III, § 311</ref>, <date date="1978-11-09">Nov. 9, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/3154">92 Stat. 3154</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a179195-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id7a179196-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I87" topic="definitions" id="id7a179197-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Definitions</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The definitions of Secretary and Commission in <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s2602">section 2602 of Title 16</ref>, Conservation, apply to this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
